{
  "texts": [
    "Using \"winsorizing\" can trim extreme values, which will avoid the difficulties associated with small values of e * t [144], but adds some complexity to the calculation and a level of arbitrariness as the amount of trimming must be specified.Rather than use relative errors, one can use relative measures.",
    "For example, let MAE b denote the MAE from the benchmark method.",
    "Then, a relative MAE is given byrelMAE = MAE/MAE b.",
    "(18)An advantage of these methods is their interpretability.",
    "However, they require several forecasts on the same series to compute MAE (or MSE)."
  ]
}